<dd> </dd>
<dd><b>Nominator&#39;s rationale: Delete</b> - Maintaining such a categorization scheme would be a shockingly bad idea. Do we want one one of these &#34;by access&#34; categories for <i>every single book</i>? As this category is titled, it is for an individual book (hell, individual <i>edition</i> of a book, in fact). Keeping sets precedent to do so. It&#39;s great this user is willing to help via use of this source, but we definitely shouldn&#39;t have this sort of system for individual books, else we set the stage for tens of thousands of sparsely populated categories. <a href="" title="User:VegaDark">VegaDark</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:VegaDark">talk</a>) 13:47, 7 June 2009 (UTC)</dd></dl>


